	open terminal /ppiirone
		>> cd ..
		>> cd ..
		>> cd etc
		>> cat resolv.conf
	to check if information is right:
		command scutil --dns show what is domain and IP address of DNS server
			we are using
		OR
		system preferences >> network >> internet i am using (Etherenet)
		>> Advanced >> DNS >> hive.fi
#####	######		7.		#####	#####
	You may choose to use a DNS server other than your primary DNS server.
		To do this, type nslookup, followed by the name of the domain you wish
		to query, and then the name or IP address of the DNS server you wish to use.
	On this case also command nslookup who.int will show the correct answer.
		but in some cases it can't find the external DNS server.
